Mix cornstarch, broth and black pepper until smooth. Set aside. Spray skillet with cooking spray and heat over medium-high heat 1 min. Cook chops 10 min. or until browned. Set chops aside. Remove skillet from heat. Spray skillet with cooking spray. Add onion. Cook over medium heat until crisp-tender. Stir cornstarch mixture and add. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly. Return chops to skillet. Cover and cook over low heat 5 min. or until chops are done.